honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class IrDAConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.IrDAConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class IrDAConfiguration
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {IR?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    DVDirect Version
    IDIrDA Nickname
    INIrDA Name
    IVIrDA Version
    PIR Protocol
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • IrDAConfiguration

        public IrDAConfiguration(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

      • getDirectVersion_IsPresent

        public boolean getDirectVersion_IsPresent()
        Indicates if getDirectVersion() parameter is present.

        This function is useful to determine if the given parameter is supported on the current printer. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned by the parameter getDirectVersion() may not be valid.

        Returns:
        If the parameter is present and valid true, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        getDirectVersion()
